A public policy analyst, Mr Kufre James, who made the call, said Nigerians should be careful in choosing a leader at the next general election because it will determine the peace and progress of the country. Kufre, who spoke in Abuja, described the immediate-past governor of Imo State, Senator Rochas Okorocha, as a candidate for the Nigerian youths in the 2023 presidential election. He said having been a governor for eight years and Senator for almost four years, Okorocha understands that true allegiance is owed to the Nigerian people and to the constitution. He said as governor, Okorocha showed remarkable courage as a leader, adding that he carried out robust and courageous town-planning expansion in the state. He added that such kind of courage and vision were essential and necessary for todayâ€™s president, adding that Okorocha placed a high premium on education. He said the country needed a president that has elaborate plans for security, law and order and what to do to grow the economy and achieve greatness as a country. He described Okorocha as a choice that satisfy the zoning consensus without sacrificing merit, while calling on good spirited Nigerians to rally support for the former govenor.